# Frontend Rules

`AGENTS.md` and nearest app-level instructions are authoritative.

## Stack

- Prefer the target app's existing framework version and conventions.
- For Next.js work, use App Router patterns unless the app already proves otherwise.
- Use React and TypeScript patterns already present in the target app.

## UI Structure

- Follow local folder naming and component patterns.
- Keep components focused; extract subcomponents only when it reduces real complexity.
- Preserve accessibility: semantic HTML, labels, keyboard behavior, and visible focus.
- Do not put real PHI or patient identifiers in UI examples, screenshots, fixtures, or stories.

## Design Tokens

- Use existing app or package design tokens before adding literals.
- Avoid hardcoded color literals in component files unless the app explicitly allows it.
- If a new token is required, define it in the token source and update usage in the same task.

## State And Data

- Prefer server data flow and URL state where the app already uses it.
- Avoid adding Redux/Zustand or new UI dependencies without explicit approval.
- Do not use `useEffect` for initial data fetching when the app has server-side patterns available.

## Reference Patterns

- Shared UI: `@packages/shared/sentra-ui`
- Design tokens: `@packages/shared/design-token`
- App-specific patterns: nearest files in the same app.
